How to create a working AmbulantPlayer for OLPC 1st generation build 767 on Fedora 9.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

For OLPC with XO build 767 (compatible with Fedora 9) I installed following additional
packages using yum:

Fedora 9> sudo yum install autoconf automake gcc-c++ libtool gettextize gettext-devel gtk2-devel pygtk2-devel

Then ./create-xo-installer creates an auto-install file in:

Fedora 9> ./tmp/ambulant-xo-installer.sh 

to be executed (after copying to olpc home dir e.g. using wifi or an USB disk)
on a compatible XO machine by executing this script as super-user:

olpc@xo> sudo ./ambulant-xo-installer.sh 

